In this speech given at the George Bush Center for Intelligence, President Biden expresses his gratitude and respect for the intelligence community. He mentions his long-standing involvement with the agency, dating back 52 years. He also pays tribute to Japanese Prime Minister Abe, who recently passed away, and emphasizes the impact of his assassination on the Japanese people. The President commends the intelligence community for their commitment to keeping the country safe and acknowledges the sacrifices made by intelligence professionals. He highlights the importance of receiving accurate and unvarnished assessments from the intelligence community and emphasizes the need for transparency and the power of example in American leadership. President Biden also emphasizes the importance of diversity within the intelligence community and acknowledges the demanding nature of their work. He concludes by expressing his respect for the CIA and his confidence in their continued service to the nation's security.